<h2>Hope</h2>
<br>
<img src="data:image/jpeg;base64," width="400" height="240">
<br>
<h2>Meaning of Hope</h2>
<img src="https://rickfyffe.files.wordpress.com/2017/09/god-lending-a-hand.png" width="400" height="240">
<br>
<br>
<br>
Hope is an optimistic state of mind that is based on an expectation <br> of positive outcomes with respect to events and circumstances <br> in one's life or the world at large. As a verb, its definitions include: <br> "expect with confidence" and "to cherish a desire with anticipation."
<br>
<br>
<img src="https://researchdigest.files.wordpress.com/2013/09/e1ce7-hope.jpg" width="400" height="240">
<br>
<h2>Cause of Having Hope</h2>
Connections with proper, positive people, a higher power, <br> and the web of life. Regeneration in all forms as stimulated <br> by breathing, sleep, meditation, prayer, spirit, impermanence, <br> and quiet. Witnessing or experiencing acts of love, <br> goodness, and kindness.
<br>
<br>
<h2>Effects of Having Hope</h2>
Hope is associated with many positive outcomes, including <br> greater happiness, better academic achievement and even <br> lowered risk of death. It's a necessary ingredient <br> for getting through tough times, of course, <br> but also for meeting everyday goals.
<br>
